Data Visualization¶

In [26]:
# Converting the 'Date' column to a datetime format
crime_data_df['Reported_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(crime_data_df['Reported_Date'])

new_crime_data_df=crime_data_df.copy()

# Extracting the year and month from the 'Date' column
new_crime_data_df['Year'] = new_crime_data_df['Reported_Date'].dt.year
new_crime_data_df['Month'] = new_crime_data_df['Reported_Date'].dt.month


# Grouping by year and month and calculating the count of occurrences
crime_counts = new_crime_data_df.groupby(['Year', 'Month']).size().reset_index(name='Count')

# Creating a pivot table for plotting
pivot_table = crime_counts.pivot(index='Year', columns='Month', values='Count')

# Creating a heatmap to visualize crime occurrences by year and month
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.title('Crime Occurrences by Year and Month')
sns.heatmap(pivot_table, cmap='YlOrRd', annot=True, fmt='g', linewidths=0.5)
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Year')
plt.show()
In [27]:
# getting the top n most frequent offense description
top_n = 15
top_descriptions = crime_data_df["Description"].value_counts().head(top_n)

# creating bar plot
sns.barplot(x=top_descriptions.index, y=top_descriptions.values)
plt.xticks(rotation=90,fontsize=8)
plt.xlabel('Description')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.title(f'Top {top_n} Most Frequent Offense Descriptions')
plt.tight_layout()  #Adjusting layout for better spacing
plt.show()
In [28]:
# Converting the 'Reported_Date' column to a datetime format
new_crime_data_df['Reported_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(new_crime_data_df['Reported_Date'])

# Extracting the month from the 'Reported_Date' column
new_crime_data_df['Month'] = new_crime_data_df['Reported_Date'].dt.month

# Grouping by month and count the number of incidents
incidents_by_month = new_crime_data_df.groupby('Month').size()

# Creating a line plot for the number of incidents over months
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(incidents_by_month.index, incidents_by_month.values, marker='o')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Number of Incidents')
plt.title('Number of Incidents Over Months in Year 2015')
plt.xticks(range(1,13),['Jan','Feb','March','April','May','June','July','Aug','Sept','Oct','Nov','Dec'])
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
In [29]:
# Group by the "Race" column and count occurrences
sex_counts = crime_data_df['Sex'].value_counts()

# Mapping for label clarity
label_mapping={'M':'Male','F':'Female','U':'Undisclosed','Unknown':'Unknown'}
sex_counts.index=sex_counts.index.map(label_mapping)

# Creating pie plot for visualizing sex distribution
plt.pie(sex_counts,labels=sex_counts.index,autopct='%1.1f%%',startangle=140)
plt.title('Distribution of Sexes')
plt.show()
